<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-30T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="466" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>During a conversation on September 12, 1947, the Secretary of State
                                and French Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_BH1">Bonnet</persName>
                                discussed the question of the future regime for the Ruhr; see
                                    <persName corresp="#p_HJD1">John Hickerson</persName>’s
                                memorandum of the conversation, in the documentation on concern of
                                the United States with political and economic developments relating
                                to France, in <ref target="frus1947v03">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>
                                </ref>.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>